Happiness and strife<br>
Comfort and pain<br>
All exist to make the other just a bit more sweeter<br>
<br>
For without pain and loss,<br>
None could appreciate what they have had<br>
Without happiness, sadness would be accepted as a normality<br>
And the sting of it would cease.<br>
<br>
To be a mortal without feeling<br>
To be without hope for change<br>
Without joy or pain<br>
Is to be empty<br>
<br>
Knowing this, would you choose pain to be no more, no matter how bitter?<br>
Would you choose to have no troubles or cares?<br>
Some of you may say yes, you suffer a pain that is great and perhaps believe you will never smile again.<br>
But if one day, when chance comes along, you encounter something that could make you smile despite your pain, would you give up that chance?<br>
<br>
Would a brief relief from suffering with a simple smile upon your face be worse than eternally being without pain, at the cost of being without joy and love?<br>
Questions each person can only answer for themselves.<br>
I know my answers.<br>
Do you?<br>
<br>
<br>
